description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if during the NFL Games Scheduled for Thanksgiving Day on November 28, 2024 all of the following occurs:

-In the game between the Detroit Lions and Chicago Bears: Jared Goff records at least 1 Total Touchdown (Rushing, Receiving, and Passing will all count towards this total)

-In the game between the Dallas Cowboys and the New York Giants: there is at least one interception thrown by any player on either team

-In the game between the Green Bay Packers and Miami Dolphins: Tyreek Hill, Josh Jacobs, and Jaylen Waddle combine for 2 or more total touchdowns.

If a relevant game is canceled or postponed beyond December 5, 2024 this market will resolve to "No".

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the NFL; however, a consensus of credible reporting will also be used.
